metadata.editComments:
Unfortunately Hooktheory doesn't allow the use of triplets or compound time signatures, so I had to transcribe this section as if it were 6/4 time -- it's actually 12/8. The key starts as if it's transitioning from B minor to B major, but then hops over to D# minor.

An interesting note about this whole track is that it seems to be tuned in "scientific pitch" -- C4 = 256 Hz, as opposed to the A440 standard that most of us are used to. Strangely enough, despite the fact that this corresponds to a tuning 40 cents flatter than A440, it's not at all obvious (and doesn't sound out of tune) unless one compares it to a pitch in standard tuning. (However, it *does* make Hookpad editing a nightmare.)
